AB  - In 2015, Southern Africa experienced a drought that affected approximately 30 million people across seven countries. Using a nationally representative household panel survey data set and a remotely sensed measure of drought intensity during the 2015-16 farming season, we rigorously estimate the short-term effects of the drought on food insecurity and child malnutrition in Malawi, and the mitigating effect of a humanitarian transfer programme.
