AB  - Four papers examine the relationship between climate change strategies and innovation, considering the role of climate-induced innovation in the context of climate change mitigation technologies as well as climate change adaptation strategies. Papers discuss climate change and environmental innovations; the impact of agricultural patents on European farmers' technical efficiency based on both unobservable heterogeneity and heteroskedasticity in the inefficiency term; different innovations in Ghana's cocoa sector, how they aim to address sustainable cocoa cultivation, and the challenges to their adoption; and evidence of good practices and innovative strategies for upgrading the climate-smart agriculture approach to mitigation and adaptation strategies through development agencies and civil society, research, and academia. Coromaldi is Associate Professor of Public Economics and Environmental Economics at the University of Rome Niccolo Cusano. Auci is Associate Professor of Economics at the University of Palermo. Index.
