AB  - Ten papers explore sustainability challenges and policy issues in the Iranian agricultural sector, covering risk management and climate change, natural resources and environmental economics, and agricultural prices and commodity market analysis. Papers discuss agricultural risk management through weather-based crop insurance for rain-fed wheat; the value at risk and conditional value at risk of food industry companies' stock portfolios on the Tehran stock market; the effects of climate change on the land share of annual crop groups; the nonuse value and related compensative surplus of Arasbaran forests; optimized reservoir management for meeting conflicting stakeholder preferences in the West Azerbaijan province; Iranian farmers' willingness to pay for integrated pest management; the validity of the law of one price in Iranian broiler and egg markets; the relationship between marketing mix and customer satisfaction with Iranian dairy companies; the long-run neutrality and superneutrality of money in Iran's agricultural sector; and the correlation between oil prices and exchange rates with input prices for the livestock and poultry industry from 1995 to 2004 and from 2005 to 2014. Rashidghalam is Researcher in the Department of Agricultural Economics at the University of Tabriz. Index.
