AB  - Twelve papers explore efforts across India, made by different corporations in collaboration with the International Crops Research Institute for the Semi-Arid Tropics (ICRISAT), to undertake corporate social responsibility (CSR) initiatives that improve rural livelihoods. Papers discuss the philosophy, policy, and practice of CSR in India; a holistic approach for achieving impact through CSR; building soil health, improving carbon footprints, and minimizing greenhouse gas emissions through CSR; a JSW Foundation case study of CSR and climate resilient agriculture; improving livelihoods through watershed interventions; a case study from Asian Paints Limited; improving water availability and diversification of cropping systems in pilot villages of North and Southern India; scaling-up of science-led development and the Sir Dorabji Tata Trust Initiative; increasing agricultural productivity of farming systems in parts of Central India and the Sir Ratan Tata Trust Initiative; sustainable development of fragile low-rainfall regions and the Power Grid Corporation of India Initiative; a case study of Rural Electrification Corporation Limited on farmer-centric integrated water management, and improving rural wastewater. Wani is Director of the Research Program-Asia at ICRISAT. Raju is Theme Leader in Policy and Impact with the Research Program-Asia at ICRISAT. Index.
