AB  - Ten papers explore the impacts of climate change, focusing on the scale of these impacts, their associated policies, and people's responses to them. Papers discuss modeling coupled climate, ecosystems, and economic systems; ecology and economics in the science of anthropogenic biosphere change; natural capital and ecosystem income; environmental health economics in low and middle income countries; climate change adaptation challenges for farmers in least developed countries; selection and design of environmental policy instruments; quasi-experimental methods in environmental economics; climate change through the lens of macroeconomics; causal inference in environmental conservation and the role of institutions; and uncertainty and ambiguity in environmental economics. Index.
