AB  - Analyzes the geography and socioeconomic conditions of Northeast India's Mizoram state and explains how agricultural production and productivity can be improved to create a sustainable livelihood for farmers in the area. Discusses the geographical backdrop and sustainable livelihoods; geostrategic location, political history, and development; population and socioeconomic development; land use--agriculture and livestock farming; a livelihood analysis; climate change--people's perception, adaptation, and resilience; food security and poverty; and a sustainable livelihood approach to poverty reduction. Sati is Professor of Geography and Resource Management at Mizoram University. Vangchhia is with the Department of Geography and Resource Management in the School of Earth Sciences and Natural Resources Management at Mizoram University. No index.
