AB  - Twenty-nine papers, presented at the 2013 World Agricultural Outlook Conference and held in June in Beijing, analyze and project agricultural production and marketing, facilitate information exchange to improve food supply and demand, and contribute to enhancing world food security and sustainable global agricultural development. Papers discuss the construction of China agriculture monitoring and the early-warning system; the design and implementation of an agricultural product price short-term forecasting system; forecasting and early-warning research on the price of China's corn and late Indica rice; a decomposition study of the agricultural products price; research on the optimal combination forecasting model for vegetable prices in Hainan; the research and design of a vegetable price spatial-temporal transmission simulation; food consumption of households in poverty-stricken areas of West China--the cases of Shaanxi, Yunnan, and Guizhou; China's aquatic products supply and demand situation over the past decade; the spatial-temporal characteristics and outlook of grain consumption in China; research on an early-warning proposal of the Chinese milk market; meteorological effects on China's expected rapeseed yield; a county-level catastrophic risk assessment of crops caused by flood in northeast China; a study on fluctuation rules of meteorological phenomena stress environment in cow dominant areas of China; a study of extreme risk measurement of the Chinese soybean futures market--VaR based on GARCH model; prediction of pork prices based on a support vector machine; a study of optimal risk sharing issues for Chinese crop insurance--a case study from the government perspective; evaluating the catastrophe risk of cold damage to crop production on the provincial scale in China; the rice yield of rural households in Niger State, Nigeria; an empirical analysis of the economies of scale of natural rubber production--based on the panel data of 86 Hainan State Farm rubber farms between 1998 and 2007; research on the economic effect of grain consumption expenditure in urban and rural China; the outputs and international competitiveness of livestock products in Brazil, Russia, China, India, and South Africa--a comparative analysis; a study of the evaluation indexes for asparagus's industrial global competitiveness; industrial agglomeration in China's agricultural product processing industry; influence and evaluation of human settlement environments after rural homestead consolidation in China--evidence from typical villages in the Jiangsu province; a strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats analysis of the industrial development of Beijing's edible fungi; an analysis of the technology application of traceability management for agroproduct quality and safety in China; a text segmentation-model-based Latent Dirichlet Allocation and ontology for question answering in agriculture; research on the search technology of agricultural information based on geographical perception; and temporal changes and the influencing factor of China importing genetic resources of livestock and poultry. Xu is at the Agricultural Information Institute at the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences. Index.
