AB  - Ten papers, plus comments, explore innovative methodologies and applications of value of information research, focusing on applications in the fields of public health and space. Papers discuss the value of information in index insurance for farmers in Africa; the value of information in a risk management approach to climate change; understanding the value of business information; valuing the potential impacts of the global Earth observation system of systems--a systems dynamics approach; the informative role of advertising and experience in dynamic brand choice--an application to the ready-to-eat cereal market; the effect of public and private quality information on consumer choice in health care markets; the adoption of over-the-counter malaria diagnostics in Africa--the role of subsidies, beliefs, externalities, and competition; the value of determining global land cover for assessing climate change mitigation options; space imaging and prevention of infectious disease--Rift Valley fever; and estimating the benefits of land imagery in environmental applications--a case study in nonpoint source pollution of groundwater. Laxminarayan is with the Center for Disease Dynamics, Economics and Policy and is Research Scholar at Princeton University. Macauley is with Resources for the Future. Index.
