AB  - Examines why poor African farmers are being denied access to productive technologies based on an opposition to farm science in more prosperous regions. Discusses why Africans are rejecting biotechnology; why rich countries dislike agricultural genetically modified organisms; downgrading agricultural science in rich countries; withdrawing support for agricultural science in Africa; keeping genetically engineered crops out of Africa; and whether drought-tolerant crops are only for the rich. Paarlberg is Betty Freyhof Johnson Professor of Political Science at Wellesley College. Index.
