AB  - This paper is an attempt to understand the dynamics of System of Rice Intensification (SRI) in water scarce regions in India. It tries to assess the potential of SRI in terms of land and water productivities in the context of drought-prone Anantapur district of Andhra Pradesh. Forty SRI practicing farmers spread over 12 mandals and 21 villages were identified for the purpose of the study. Plot wise information pertaining to 40 SRI and 34 traditional paddy plots were collected from these farmers during May-June 2005 and the collected data were analysed separately by using descriptive statistics like averages, variances etc. The study focused on the relative advantages of SRI in terms of profitability, resource use, risks etc. It provides valuable insight regarding the potential and risks involved in SRI adoption.
